quran[149]{c,v,t}:
  5,82,You will surely find the most bitter towards the believers to be the Jews and polytheists and the most gracious to be those who call themselves Christian. That is because there are priests and monks among them and because they are not arrogant
  5,83,"When they listen to what has been revealed to the Messenger, you see their eyes overflowing with tears for recognizing the truth. They say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We believe, so count us among the witnesses"
  5,84,Why should we not believe in God and the truth that has come to us? And we long for our Lord to include us in the company of the righteous.‚ÄĚ
  5,85,"So God will reward them for what they said with Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. And that is the reward of the good-doers"
  5,86,"As for those who disbelieve and reject Our signs, they will be the residents of the Hellfire"
  5,87,"O believers! Do not forbid the good things which God has made lawful for you, and do not transgress. Indeed, God does not like transgressors"
  5,88,"Eat of the good, lawful things provided to you by God. And be mindful of God in Whom you believe"
  5,89,"God will not call you to account for your thoughtless oaths, but He will hold you accountable for deliberate oaths. The penalty for a broken oath is to feed ten poor people from what you normally feed your own family, or to clothe them, or to free a bondsperson. But if none of this is affordable, then you must fast three days. This is the penalty for breaking your oaths. So be mindful of your oaths. This is how God makes things clear to you, so perhaps you will be grateful"
  5,90,"O believers! Intoxicants, gambling, idols, and drawing lots for decisions¬†are all evil of Satan‚Äôs handiwork. So shun them so you may be successful"
  5,91,Satan‚Äôs plan is to stir up hostility and hatred between you with intoxicants and gambling and to prevent you from remembering God and praying. Will you not then abstain
  5,92,"Obey God and obey the Messenger and beware! But if you turn away, then know that Our Messenger‚Äôs duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ clearly"
  5,93,"There is no blame on those who believe and do good for what they had consumed before ňĻthe prohibitionňļ, as long as they fear God, have faith, and do what is good; then they believe and act virtuously, then become fully mindful ňĻof Godňļ and do righteous deeds. For God loves the good-doers"
  5,94,O believers! God will surely test you with game within the reach of your hands and spears to distinguish those who fear Him in secret. Whoever transgresses from now on will suffer a painful punishment
  5,95,"O believers! Do not kill game while on pilgrimage. Whoever kills game intentionally must compensate by offering its equivalence‚ÄĒas judged by two just men among you‚ÄĒto be offered at the Sacred House, or by feeding the needy, or by fasting so that they may taste the consequences of their violations. God has forgiven what has been done. But those who persist will be punished by God. And God is Almighty, capable of punishment"
  5,96,"It is lawful for you to hunt and eat seafood, as a provision for you and for travellers. But hunting on land is forbidden to you while on pilgrimage. Be mindful of God to Whom you all will be gathered"
  5,97,"God has made the Ka‚Äôbah‚ÄĒthe Sacred House‚ÄĒa sanctuary of well-being for all people, along with the sacred months, the sacrificial animals, and the ňĻofferings decorated withňļ garlands. All this so you may know that God knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth, and that He has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of everything"
  5,98,"Know that God is severe in punishment and that He is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  5,99,The Messenger‚Äôs duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ. And God ňĻfullyňļ knows what you reveal and what you conceal
  5,100,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúGood and evil are not equal, though you may be dazzled by the abundance of evil. So be mindful of God, O people of reason, so you may be successful.‚ÄĚ"
  5,101,"O believers! Do not ask about any matter which, if made clear to you, may disturb you. But if you inquire about what is being revealed in the Quran, it will be made clear to you. God has forgiven what was done ňĻin the pastňļ.¬†And God is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  5,102,Some people before you asked such questions then denied their answers
  5,103,"God has never ordained the ňĻso-calledňļ baŠł•√ģrah, s√Ę'ibah, waŠĻ£√ģlah, and Šł•√Ęm¬†camels.¬†But the disbelievers¬†just fabricate lies about God, and most of them lack understanding"
  5,104,"When it is said to them, ‚ÄúCome to God‚Äôs revelations and to the Messenger,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúWhat we found our forefathers practicing is good enough for us.‚ÄĚ ňĻWould they still do so,ňļ even if their forefathers had absolutely no knowledge or guidance"
  5,105,"O believers! You are accountable only for yourselves.¬†It will not harm you if someone chooses to deviate‚ÄĒas long as you are ňĻrightlyňļ guided. To God you will all return, and He will inform you of what you used to do"
  5,106,"O believers! When death approaches any of you, call upon two just Muslim men to witness as you make a bequest; otherwise, two non-Muslims if you are afflicted with death while on a journey.¬†If you doubt ňĻtheir testimonyňļ, keep them after prayer and let them testify under oath ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúBy God! We would never sell our testimony for any price, even in favour of a close relative, nor withhold the testimony of God. Otherwise, we would surely be sinful.‚ÄĚ"
  5,107,"If they are found guilty ňĻof false testimonyňļ, let the deceased‚Äôs two closest heirs affected by the bequest replace the witnesses and testify under oath ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúBy God! Our testimony is truer than theirs. We have not transgressed. Otherwise, we would surely be wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  5,108,In this way it is more likely that witnesses will give true testimony or else fear that their oaths could be refuted by those of the heirs. Be mindful of God and obey. For God does not guide the rebellious people
  5,109,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day God will gather the messengers and say, ‚ÄúWhat response did you receive?‚ÄĚ They will reply, ‚ÄúWe have no knowledge ňĻcompared to Youňļ! You ňĻaloneňļ are indeed the Knower of all unseen.‚ÄĚ"
  5,110,"And ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ God will say, ‚ÄúO Jesus, son of Mary! Remember My favour upon you and your mother: how I supported you with the holy spirit¬†so you spoke to people in ňĻyourňļ infancy and adulthood. How I taught you writing, wisdom, the Torah, and the Gospel. How you moulded a bird from clay‚ÄĒby My Will‚ÄĒand breathed into it and it became a ňĻrealňļ bird‚ÄĒby My Will. How you healed the blind and the lepers‚ÄĒby My Will. How you brought the dead to life‚ÄĒby My Will. How I prevented the Children of Israel from harming you when you came to them with clear proofs and the disbelievers among them said, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  5,111,"And how I inspired the disciples, ‚ÄúBelieve in Me and My messenger!‚ÄĚ They declared, ‚ÄúWe believe and bear witness that we fully submit ňĻto Godňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  5,112,"ňĻRememberňļ when the disciples asked, ‚ÄúO Jesus, son of Mary! Would your Lord be willing to send down to us a table spread with food from heaven?‚ÄĚ Jesus answered, ‚ÄúFear God if you are ňĻtrulyňļ believers.‚ÄĚ"
  5,113,"They said, ‚ÄúWe ňĻonlyňļ wish to eat from it to reassure our hearts, to verify you are indeed truthful to us, and to become its witnesses.‚ÄĚ"
  5,114,"Jesus, son of Mary, prayed, ‚ÄúO God, our Lord! Send us from heaven a table spread with food as a feast for us‚ÄĒthe first and last of us‚ÄĒand as a sign from You. Provide for us! You are indeed the Best Provider.‚ÄĚ"
  5,115,"God answered, ‚ÄúI am sending it down to you. But whoever among you denies afterwards will be subjected to a torment I have never inflicted on anyone of My creation.‚ÄĚ"
  5,116,"And ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ God will say, ‚ÄúO Jesus, son of Mary! Did you ever ask the people to worship you and your mother as gods besides God?‚ÄĚ He will answer, ‚ÄúGlory be to You! How could I ever say what I had no right to say? If I had said such a thing, you would have certainly known it. You know what is ňĻhiddenňļ within me, but I do not know what is within You. Indeed, You ňĻaloneňļ are the Knower of all unseen"
  5,117,"I never told them anything except what You ordered me to say: ‚ÄúWorship God‚ÄĒmy Lord and your Lord!‚ÄĚ And I was witness over them as long as I remained among them. But when You took me,¬†You were the Witness over them‚ÄĒand You are a Witness over all things"
  5,118,"If You punish them, they belong to You after all.¬†But if You forgive them, You are surely the Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  5,119,"God will declare, ‚ÄúThis is the Day when ňĻonlyňļ the faithful will benefit from their faithfulness. Theirs are Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. God is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. That is the ultimate triumph.‚ÄĚ"
  5,120,To God ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything within. And He is Most Capable of everything
  6,1,All praise is for God Who created the heavens and the earth and made darkness and light.¬†Yet the disbelievers set up equals to their Lord ňĻin worshipňļ
  6,2,"He is the One Who created you from clay,¬†then appointed a term ňĻfor your deathňļ and another known only to Him ňĻfor your resurrectionňļ‚ÄĒyet you continue to doubt"
  6,3,"He is the Only True God in the heavens and the earth. He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal, and knows whatever you do"
  6,4,"Whenever a sign comes to them from their Lord, they turn away from it"
  6,5,"They have indeed rejected the truth when it came to them, so they will soon face the consequences of their ridicule"
  6,6,Have they not seen how many ňĻdisbelievingňļ peoples¬†We destroyed before them? We had made them more established in the land than you. We sent down abundant rain for them and made rivers flow at their feet. Then We destroyed them for their sins and replaced them with other peoples
  6,7,"Had We sent down to you ňĻO Prophetňļ a revelation in writing and they were to touch it with their own hands, the disbelievers would still have said, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but pure magic!‚ÄĚ"
  6,8,"They say, ‚ÄúWhy has no ňĻvisibleňļ angel come with him?‚ÄĚ Had We sent down an angel, the matter would have certainly been settled ňĻat onceňļ,¬†and they would have never been given more time ňĻto repentňļ"
  6,9,"And if We had sent an angel, We would have certainly made it ňĻassume the form ofňļ a man‚ÄĒleaving them more confused than they already are"
  6,10,"ňĻOtherňļ messengers had already been ridiculed before you ňĻO Prophetňļ, but those who mocked them were overtaken by what they used to ridicule"
  6,11,"Say, ‚ÄúTravel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers.‚ÄĚ"
  6,12,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúTo whom belongs everything in the heavens and the earth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúTo God!‚ÄĚ He has taken upon Himself to be Merciful. He will certainly gather ňĻall ofňļ you together for the Day of Judgment‚ÄĒabout which there is no doubt. But those who have ruined themselves will never believe"
  6,13,"To Him belongs whatever exists in the day and night. And He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  6,14,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWill I take any guardian other than God, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, Who provides for all and is not in need of provision?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúI have been commanded to be the first to submit and not be one of the polytheists.‚ÄĚ"
  6,15,"Say, ‚ÄúI truly fear‚ÄĒif I were to disobey my Lord‚ÄĒthe torment of a tremendous Day.‚ÄĚ"
  6,16,Whoever is spared the torment of that Day will have certainly been shown God‚Äôs mercy. And that is the absolute triumph
  6,17,"If God touches you with harm, none can undo it except Him. And if He touches you with a blessing, He is Most Capable of everything"
  6,18,"He reigns supreme over His creation. And He is the All-Wise, All-Aware"
  6,19,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho is the best witness?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúGod is! He is a Witness between me and you. And this Quran has been revealed to me so that, with it, I may warn you and whoever it reaches. Do you ňĻpagansňļ testify that there are other gods besides God?‚ÄĚ ňĻThenňļ say, ‚ÄúI will never testify ňĻto thisňļ!‚ÄĚ ňĻAndňļ say, ‚ÄúThere is only One God. And I totally reject whatever ňĻidolsňļ you associate with Him.‚ÄĚ"
  6,20,Those to whom We gave the Scripture recognize him ňĻto be a true prophetňļ as they recognize their own children. Those who have ruined themselves will never believe
  6,21,"Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against God or deny His signs? Indeed, the wrongdoers will never succeed"
  6,22,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day We will gather them all together then ask those who associated others ňĻwith God in worshipňļ, ‚ÄúWhere are those gods you used to claim?‚ÄĚ"
  6,23,"Their only argument will be: ‚ÄúBy God, our Lord! We were never polytheists.‚ÄĚ"
  6,24,See how they will lie about themselves and how those ňĻgodsňļ they fabricated will fail them
  6,25,"There are some of them who ňĻpretend toňļ listen to your recitation ňĻof the Quranňļ, but We have cast veils over their hearts‚ÄĒleaving them unable to comprehend it‚ÄĒand deafness in their ears. Even if they were to see every sign, they still would not believe in them. The disbelievers would ňĻevenňļ come to argue with you, saying, ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ is nothing but ancient fables!‚ÄĚ"
  6,26,"They turn others away from the Prophet and distance themselves as well. They ruin none but themselves, yet they fail to perceive it"
  6,27,"If only you could see when they will be detained before the Fire! They will cry, ‚ÄúOh! If only we could be sent back, we would never deny the signs of our Lord and we would ňĻsurelyňļ be of the believers.‚ÄĚ"
  6,28,"But no! ňĻThey only say thisňļ because the truth they used to hide will become all too clear to them. Even if they were to be sent back, they would certainly revert to what they were forbidden. Indeed they are liars"
  6,29,"They insisted, ‚ÄúThere is nothing beyond this worldly life and we will never be resurrected.‚ÄĚ"
  6,30,"But if only you could see when they will be detained before their Lord! He will ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúIs this ňĻHereafterňļ not the truth?‚ÄĚ They will cry, ‚ÄúAbsolutely, by our Lord!‚ÄĚ He will say, ‚ÄúThen taste the punishment for your disbelief.‚ÄĚ"
  6,31,"Losers indeed are those who deny the meeting with God until the Hour takes them by surprise, then they will cry, ‚ÄúWoe to us for having ignored this!‚ÄĚ They will bear ňĻthe burden ofňļ their sins on their backs. Evil indeed is their burden"
  6,32,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement, but far better is the ňĻeternalňļ Home of the Hereafter for those mindful ňĻof Godňļ. Will you not then understand"
  6,33,We certainly know that what they say grieves you ňĻO Prophetňļ. It is not your honesty they question‚ÄĒit is God‚Äôs signs that the wrongdoers deny
  6,34,"Indeed, messengers before you were rejected but patiently endured rejection and persecution until Our help came to them. And God‚Äôs promise ňĻto helpňļ is never broken. And you have already received some of the narratives of these messengers"
  6,35,"If you find their denial unbearable, then build‚ÄĒif you can‚ÄĒa tunnel through the earth or stairs to the sky to bring them a ňĻmore compellingňļ sign. Had God so willed, He could have guided them all. So do not be one of those ignorant ňĻof this factňļ"
  6,36,"Only the attentive will respond ňĻto your callňļ. As for the dead, God will raise them up, then to Him they will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  6,37,"They ask, ‚ÄúWhy has no ňĻotherňļ sign been sent down to him from his Lord?‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúGod certainly has the power to send down a sign‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒthough most of them do not know"
  6,38,All living beings roaming the earth and winged birds soaring in the sky are communities like yourselves.¬†We have left nothing out of the Record.¬†Then to their Lord they will be gathered all together
  6,39,Those who deny Our signs are ňĻwilfullyňļ deaf and dumb‚ÄĒlost in darkness. God leaves whoever He wills to stray and guides whoever He wills to the Straight Way
  6,40,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if you were overwhelmed by God‚Äôs torment or the Hour‚ÄĒwould you call upon any other than God ňĻfor helpňļ? ňĻAnswer meňļ if your claims are true"
  6,41,"No! He is the only One you would call. And if He willed, He could remove the affliction that made you invoke Him. Only then will you forget whatever you associate with Him ňĻin worshipňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  6,42,"Indeed, We have sent messengers before you ňĻO Prophetňļ to other people who We put through suffering and adversity ňĻfor their denialňļ, so perhaps they would be humbled"
  6,43,"Why did they not humble themselves when We made them suffer? Instead, their hearts were hardened, and Satan made their misdeeds appealing to them"
  6,44,"When they became oblivious to warnings, We showered them with everything they desired. But just as they became prideful of what they were given, We seized them by surprise, then they instantly fell into despair"
  6,45,So the wrongdoers were utterly uprooted. And all praise is for God‚ÄĒLord of all worlds
  6,46,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if God were to take away your hearing or sight, or seal your hearts‚ÄĒwho else other than God could restore it?‚ÄĚ See ňĻO Prophetňļ how We vary the signs, yet they still turn away"
  6,47,"Ask, ‚ÄúImagine if God‚Äôs punishment were to overwhelm you with or without warning‚ÄĒwho would be destroyed other than the wrongdoers?‚ÄĚ"
  6,48,"We have sent messengers only as deliverers of good news and as warners. Whoever believes and does good, there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  6,49,But those who deny Our signs will be afflicted with punishment for their rebelliousness
  6,50,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI do not say to you that I possess God‚Äôs treasuries or know the unseen, nor do I claim to be an angel. I only follow what is revealed to me.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúAre those blind ňĻto the truthňļ equal to those who can see? Will you not then reflect?‚ÄĚ"
  6,51,Warn with this ňĻQuranňļ those who are awed by the prospect of being gathered before their Lord‚ÄĒwhen they will have no protector or intercessor besides Him‚ÄĒso perhaps they will be mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  6,52,"ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Do not dismiss those ňĻpoor believersňļ who invoke their Lord morning and evening, seeking His pleasure.¬†You are not accountable for them whatsoever, nor are they accountable for you. So do not dismiss them, or you will be one of the wrongdoers"
  6,53,"In this way We have tested some by means of others, so those ňĻdisbelieversňļ may say, ‚ÄúHas God favoured these ňĻpoor believersňļ out of all of us?‚ÄĚ Does God not best recognize the grateful"
  6,54,"When the believers in Our revelations come to you, say, ‚ÄúPeace be upon you! Your Lord has taken upon Himself to be Merciful. Whoever among you commits evil ignorantly ňĻor recklesslyňļ then repents afterwards and mends their ways, then God is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  6,55,"This is how We make Our signs clear, so the way of the wicked may become distinct"
  6,56,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI have been forbidden to worship those you invoke besides God.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúI will not follow your desires, for I then would certainly be astray and not one of those ňĻrightlyňļ guided.‚ÄĚ"
  6,57,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIndeed, I stand on a clear proof from my Lord‚ÄĒyet you have denied it. That ňĻtormentňļ you seek to hasten is not within my power. It is only God Who decides ňĻits timeňļ. He declares the truth. And He is the Best of Judges.‚ÄĚ"
  6,58,"Say ňĻalsoňļ, ‚ÄúIf what you seek to hasten were within my power, the matter between us would have already been settled. But God knows the wrongdoers best.‚ÄĚ"
  6,59,"With Him are the keys of the unseen‚ÄĒno one knows them except Him.¬†And He knows what is in the land and sea. Not even a leaf falls without His knowledge, nor a grain in the darkness of the earth or anything‚ÄĒgreen or dry‚ÄĒbut is ňĻwrittenňļ in a perfect Record"
  6,60,"He is the One Who calls back your souls by night and knows what you do by day, then revives you daily to complete your appointed term. To Him is your ňĻultimateňļ return, then He will inform you of what you used to do"
  6,61,"He reigns supreme over all of His creation, and sends recording-angels, watching over you. When death comes to any of you, Our angels take their soul, never neglecting this duty"
  6,62,Then they are ňĻallňļ returned to God‚ÄĒtheir True Master. Judgment is His ňĻaloneňļ. And He is the Swiftest Reckoner
  6,63,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWho rescues you from the darkest times on land and at sea? He ňĻaloneňļ you call upon with humility, openly and secretly: ‚ÄúIf You rescue us from this, we will be ever grateful.‚ÄĚ"
  6,64,"Say, ‚ÄúňĻOnlyňļ God rescues you from this and any other distress, yet you associate others with Him ňĻin worshipňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  6,65,"Say, ‚ÄúHe ňĻaloneňļ has the power to unleash upon you a torment from above or below you or split you into ňĻconflictingňļ factions and make you taste the violence of one another.‚ÄĚ See how We vary the signs, so perhaps they will comprehend"
  6,66,"Still your people ňĻO Prophetňļ have rejected this ňĻQuranňļ, although it is the truth. Say, ‚ÄúI am not a keeper over you.‚ÄĚ"
  6,67,Every ňĻdestinedňļ matter has a ňĻsetňļ time to transpire. And you will soon come to know
  6,68,"And when you come across those who ridicule Our revelations, do not sit with them unless they engage in a different topic. Should Satan make you forget, then once you remember, do not ňĻcontinue toňļ sit with the wrongdoing people"
  6,69,"Those mindful ňĻof Godňļ will not be accountable for those ňĻwho ridicule itňļ whatsoever‚ÄĒtheir duty is to advise, so perhaps the ridiculers will abstain"
  6,70,"And leave those who take this¬†faith ňĻof Islamňļ as mere play and amusement and are deluded by ňĻtheirňļ worldly life. Yet remind them by this ňĻQuranňļ, so no one should be ruined for their misdeeds. They will have no protector or intercessor other than God. Even if they were to offer every ňĻpossibleňļ ransom, none will be accepted from them. Those are the ones who will be ruined for their misdeeds. They will have a boiling drink and painful punishment for their disbelief"
  6,71,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúShould we invoke, other than God, those ňĻidolsňļ which cannot benefit or harm us, and turn back to disbelief after God has guided us? ňĻIf we do so, we will beňļ like those disoriented by devils in the wilderness, while their companions call them to guidance, ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄėCome to us!‚Äô Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúGod‚Äôs guidance is the ňĻonlyňļ true guidance. And we are commanded to submit to the Lord of all worlds"
  6,72,"establish prayer, and be mindful of Him. To Him you will all be gathered together"
  6,73,"He is the One Who created the heavens and the earth in truth. On the Day ňĻof Judgmentňļ He will say, ‚ÄėBe!‚Äô And there will be! His command is truth. All authority is His ňĻaloneňļ¬†on the Day the Trumpet will be blown.¬†He is the Knower of all‚ÄĒseen or unseen. And He is the All-Wise, All-Aware.‚ÄĚ"
  6,74,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham said to his father, »āzar, ‚ÄúDo you take idols as gods? It is clear to me that you and your people are entirely misguided.‚ÄĚ"
  6,75,"We also showed Abraham the wonders of the heavens and the earth, so he would be sure in faith"
  6,76,"When the night grew dark upon him, he saw a star and said, ‚ÄúThis is my Lord!‚ÄĚ But when it set, he said, ‚ÄúI do not love things that set.‚ÄĚ"
  6,77,"Then when he saw the moon rising, he said, ‚ÄúThis one is my Lord!‚ÄĚ But when it disappeared, he said, ‚ÄúIf my Lord does not guide me, I will certainly be one of the misguided people.‚ÄĚ"
  6,78,"Then when he saw the sun shining, he said, ‚ÄúThis must be my Lord‚ÄĒit is the greatest!‚ÄĚ But again when it set, he declared, ‚ÄúO my people! I totally reject whatever you associate ňĻwith God in worshipňļ"
  6,79,I have turned my face towards the One Who has originated the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒbeing upright‚ÄĒand I am not one of the polytheists.‚ÄĚ
  6,80,"And his people argued with him. He responded, ‚ÄúAre you arguing with me about God, while He has guided me? I am not afraid of whatever ňĻidolsňļ you associate with Him‚ÄĒňĻnone can harm me,ňļ unless my Lord so wills. My Lord encompasses everything in ňĻHisňļ knowledge. Will you not be mindful"
  6,81,"And how should I fear your associate-gods, while you have no fear in associating ňĻothersňļ with God‚ÄĒa practice He has never authorized? Which side has more right to security? ňĻTell meňļ if you really know!‚ÄĚ"
  6,82,It is ňĻonlyňļ those who are faithful and do not tarnish their faith with falsehood¬†who are guaranteed security and are ňĻrightlyňļ guided
  6,83,"This was the argument We gave Abraham against his people. We elevate in rank whoever We please. Surely your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,84,"And We blessed him with Isaac and Jacob. We guided them all as We previously guided Noah and those among his descendants: David, Solomon, Job, Joseph, Moses, and Aaron. This is how We reward the good-doers"
  6,85,"Likewise, ňĻWe guidedňļ Zachariah, John, Jesus, and Elias, who were all of the righteous"
  6,86,"ňĻWe also guidedňļ Ishmael, Elisha, Jonah, and Lot, favouring each over other people ňĻof their timeňļ"
  6,87,"And ňĻWe favouredňļ some of their forefathers, their descendants, and their brothers. We chose them and guided them to the Straight Path"
  6,88,"This is God‚Äôs guidance with which He guides whoever He wills of His servants. Had they associated others with Him ňĻin worshipňļ, their ňĻgoodňļ deeds would have been wasted"
  6,89,"Those were the ones to whom We gave the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood. But if these ňĻpagansňļ disbelieve in this ňĻmessageňļ, then We have already entrusted it to a people who will never disbelieve in it"
  6,90,"These ňĻprophetsňļ were ňĻrightlyňļ guided by God, so follow their guidance. Say, ‚ÄúI ask no reward of you for this ňĻQuranňļ‚ÄĒit is a reminder to the whole world.‚ÄĚ"
  6,91,"And they¬†have not shown God His proper reverence when they said, ‚ÄúGod has revealed nothing to any human being.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWho then revealed the Book brought forth by Moses as a light and guidance for people, which you split into separate sheets‚ÄĒrevealing some and hiding much? You have been taught ňĻthrough this Quranňļ what neither you nor your forefathers knew.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúGod ňĻrevealed itňļ!‚ÄĚ Then leave them to amuse themselves with falsehood"
  6,92,This is a blessed Book which We have revealed‚ÄĒconfirming what came before it‚ÄĒso you may warn the Mother of Cities¬†and everyone around it. Those who believe in the Hereafter ňĻtrulyňļ believe in it and guard their prayers
  6,93,"Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies against God or claims, ‚ÄúI have received revelations!‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒalthough nothing was revealed to them‚ÄĒor the one who says, ‚ÄúI can reveal the like of God‚Äôs revelations!‚ÄĚ? If you ňĻO Prophetňļ could only see the wrongdoers in the throes of death while the angels are stretching out their hands ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúGive up your souls! Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for telling lies about God and for being arrogant towards His revelations!‚ÄĚ"
  6,94,ňĻTodayňļ you have come back to Us all alone as We created you the first time‚ÄĒleaving behind everything We have provided you with. We do not see your intercessors with you‚ÄĒthose you claimed were God‚Äôs partners ňĻin worshipňļ. All your ties have been broken and all your claims have let you down.‚ÄĚ
  6,95,"Indeed, God is the One Who causes seeds and fruit stones to sprout. He brings forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. That is God! How can you then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  6,96,"He causes the dawn to break, and has made the night for rest and ňĻmadeňļ the sun and the moon ňĻto travelňļ with precision. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  6,97,And He is the One Who has made the stars as your guide through the darkness of land and sea. We have already made the signs clear for people who know
  6,98,"And He is the One Who originated you all from a single soul,¬†then assigned you a place to live and another to ňĻbe laid toňļ rest. We have already made the signs clear for people who comprehend"
  6,99,"And He is the One Who sends down rain from the sky‚ÄĒcausing all kinds of plants to grow‚ÄĒproducing green stalks from which We bring forth clustered grain. And from palm trees come clusters of dates hanging within reach. ňĻThere areňļ also gardens of grapevines, olives, and pomegranates, similar ňĻin shapeňļ but dissimilar ňĻin tasteňļ. Look at their fruit as it yields and ripens! Indeed, in these are signs for people who believe"
  6,100,"Yet they associate the jinn¬†with God ňĻin worshipňļ, even though He created them, and they falsely attribute to Him sons¬†and daughters¬†out of ignorance. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they claim"
  6,101,ňĻHe isňļ the Originator of the heavens and earth. How could He have children when He has no mate? He created all things and has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of everything
  6,102,"That is God‚ÄĒyour Lord! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. ňĻHe isňļ the Creator of all things, so worship Him ňĻaloneňļ. And He is the Maintainer of everything"
  6,103,"No vision can encompass Him, but He encompasses all vision. For He is the Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  6,104,"Indeed, there have come to you insights from your Lord. So whoever chooses to see, it is for their own good. But whoever chooses to be blind, it is to their own loss. And I am not a keeper over you"
  6,105,"And so We vary our signs to the extent that they will say, ‚ÄúYou have studied ňĻprevious scripturesňļ,‚ÄĚ¬†and We make this ňĻQuranňļ clear for people who know"
  6,106,ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Follow what is revealed to you from your Lord‚ÄĒthere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him‚ÄĒand turn away from the polytheists
  6,107,"Had God willed, they would not have been polytheists. We have not appointed you as their keeper, nor are you their maintainer"
  6,108,"ňĻO believers!ňļ Do not insult what they invoke besides God or they will insult God spitefully out of ignorance. This is how We have made each people‚Äôs deeds appealing to them. Then to their Lord is their return, and He will inform them of what they used to do"
  6,109,"They swear by God their most solemn oaths that if a sign were to come to them, they would certainly believe in it. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSigns are only with God.‚ÄĚ What will make you ňĻbelieversňļ realize that even if a sign were to come to them, they still would not believe"
  6,110,"We turn their hearts and eyes away ňĻfrom the truthňļ as they refused to believe at first, leaving them to wander blindly in their defiance"